## 2. The Center Is Not a Piece -- It Is the Point of Integration

### What the Center Is NOT

```
The center is NOT:
  - Just another small cube (it has no exterior)
  - Empty space (without it, the cube has no interior)
  - A defect or loss (it is the condition for wholeness)
  - An object to be studied from outside (it has no outer face)
```

### What the Center IS

```
The center is:
  - The point where all 26 parts CONVERGE
  - The reference that gives meaning to "interior" and "exterior"
  - The space where integration CAN OCCUR
  - The position from which everything else is experienced

Without the center:
  - The 26 parts have no common reference point
  - There is no "inside" the cube
  - The parts are a collection, not a system
  - There is no cube -- there are 26 disconnected pieces
```

### The Analogy of the Room

```
Walls, floor, ceiling = structure (the 26)
The room itself = the space they create (the 1)

The room is not the walls.
The walls are not the room.
But without walls, there is no room.
And without the room, the walls enclose nothing.

The 26 create the conditions.
The 1 is where existence happens.
```

